<td width="45%" style="text-align: center;">450°F</td>
<td width="5%" style="text-align: center;">=</td>
<td width="50%" style="text-align: center;">230°C or Gas Mark 9</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="45%" style="text-align: center;">475°F</td>
<td width="5%"style="text-align: center;">=</td>
<td width="50%"style="text-align: center;">240°C or Gas Mark 10</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<div class="indexlinks" style="text-align: justify;"><strong><a name="other">Other</a></strong></div>

<p style="text-align: justify;">And for conversions that are not listed I found a great conversion calculator <a href="http://www.cooks.com/rec/convert/">here</a>!</p>



</div>
</code></div>

<div class="domore">
